  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The infertility patients who are performed saline infusion sonohysterography (SIS) for
      studying the pathology inside the uterine cavity has pain. From pilot study the pain score is
      6.80. It will have more benefits if we can manage this procedure with less or no pain. Many
      studies have tried to decrease pain such as types of catheter, intrauterine lidocaine
      infusion. Some have real effects but no study with oral Mefenamic acid or Hyoscine before the
      procedure.The drugs are safe and easy to administration and chief.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
